id="post-2930" class="post-2930 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-energy category-transportation tag-battery tag-car tag-leaf tag-nissan"><h2 class="entry-title"><a
href="http://www.thingsaregood.com/2011/08/04/nissan-cars-may-power-your-home/" title="Permalink to Nissan Cars May Power Your Home" rel="bookmark">Nissan Cars May Power Your Home</a></h2><div
class="entry-meta"> <span
class="entry-date" title="2011/08/04 12:16 pm"><a
href="http://www.thingsaregood.com/2011/08/04/nissan-cars-may-power-your-home/" title="Nissan Cars May Power Your Home" rel="bookmark">2011/08/04 12:16 pm</a></span><span
class="entry-meta-sep"> / </span><span
class="entry-author author vcard"><a
href="http://www.thingsaregood.com/author/administrator/" title="by Adam Clare" rel="author">Adam Clare</a></span></div><div
class="entry-content clearfix"><p>Nissan has built a car that can charge on the road then use the excess charge it holds to power a home. This car can then be used to power a home in the case of a blackout or an emergency.</p><blockquote><p>The system works by linking the car via a quick charging port to the house&#8217;s electricity distribution panel. Power can also be fed the other way if the house generates its own electricity with rooftop solar panels.</p><p>The Leaf batteries have a capacity of 24 kilowatt hours when fully charged, equivalent to the electricity used by the average Japanese household in two days, said the company.</p><p>The output from the vehicle comes to six kilowatts, enough to power electricity-guzzling appliances such as a refrigerator, air conditioner and washing machine at the same time, the company said.</p></blockquote><p><a
href="http://www.google.com/hostednews/afp/article/ALeqM5gb6nCpg7n6zv_Z5S0ZTaz80kAyzA?docId=CNG.b5d6f26d26cde586fa7a9380cfa7a523.11">Read the full article here</a></p><div
class='sharedaddy sd-block sd-like jetpack-likes-widget-wrapper jetpack-likes-widget-unloaded' id='like-post-wrapper-1111807-2930-5384e986c1664' data-src='//widgets.wp.com/likes/#blog_id=1111807&amp;post_id=2930&amp;origin=www.thingsaregood.com&amp;obj_id=1111807-2930-5384e986c1664' data-name='like-post-frame-1111807-2930-5384e986c1664'><h3 class='sd-title'>Like this:</h3><div
